Package edu.uky.cs.nil.sabre.graph

Class Edge

java.lang.Object
edu.uky.cs.nil.sabre.graph.Edge
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
Direct Known Subclasses:
EpistemicEdge, TemporalEdge
public abstract class Edge extends Object implements Serializable
An directed edge in a state graph extends from a parent node to a child node and has a label explaining the meaning of the transition. There are two main types of edges in state graphs: temporal edges and epistemic edges.
Author:
Stephen G. Ware
